The changes in the fair value of Level 1 financial instruments were as follows:
From 2018 year end to 2019 year end:
• The fair value of Level 1 financial instruments increased by 0.9% from $13,865,961 to $13,966,827;
• The fair value of Level 2 financial instruments increased by 0.6% from $12,965,961 to $12,966,827;
• The fair value of Level 3 financial instruments increased by 0.1% from $11,965,961 to $11,966,827.
